1
00:00:00,792 --> 00:00:03,253
[EMIL] <i>Where are the others</i>
<i>who were with Dr. Morillo?</i>

2
00:00:03,336 --> 00:00:06,089
[GOON] <i>They got away,</i>
<i>but they're still on the island.</i>

3
00:00:06,172 --> 00:00:08,466
- [EMIL]<i> Which ones?</i>
<i>- The island's owner's son.</i>

4
00:00:08,550 --> 00:00:09,634
[GRETA] <i>What about Liam?</i>

5
00:00:09,718 --> 00:00:12,262
<i>I'm sure they'll kill Liam</i>
<i>once they find him.</i>

6
00:00:12,345 --> 00:00:14,055
<i>We need to get to him first.</i>

7
00:00:14,139 --> 00:00:17,267
[GWEN] <i>Boss Emil wants more booby traps</i>
<i>planted around the perimeter.</i>

8
00:00:17,350 --> 00:00:19,978
<i>- Is that really necessary?</i>
<i>- They've already slipped past us.</i>

9
00:00:20,061 --> 00:00:21,813
[GWEN] <i>Some of them are still out there.</i>

10
00:00:22,564 --> 00:00:24,399
- [SCREAMS, GRUNTS]
- [GUNSHOTS]

11
00:00:25,358 --> 00:00:26,526
[GUNSHOTS]

12
00:00:26,609 --> 00:00:27,777
- [FIN] <i>Chief!</i>
<i>- Wait.</i>

13
00:00:28,445 --> 00:00:31,072
- [GRETA SCREAMS]
<i>- Fine, we surrender! I'm putting it down.</i>

14
00:00:31,156 --> 00:00:32,574
- [GUNSHOTS]
- [LIAM]<i> Ma!</i>

15
00:00:32,657 --> 00:00:35,618
<i>Let's go. We're not safe here.</i>

16
00:00:35,702 --> 00:00:37,787
[OFFICER]<i> People from La Playa Roja</i>
<i>have been rescued, sir.</i>

17
00:00:37,871 --> 00:00:40,540
[JACINTO] <i>Why didn't you tell me about</i>
<i>the La Playa Roja operation?</i>

18
00:00:40,623 --> 00:00:43,209
<i>The chain of command here</i>
<i>should be going through me, not Areza.</i>

19
00:00:43,293 --> 00:00:46,212
The chain of command here goes through me.

20
00:00:46,296 --> 00:00:50,091
<i>It was my decision</i>
<i>to assign Areza to lead the operation.</i>

21
00:00:51,676 --> 00:00:54,220
<i>- Where's Grandpa?</i>
<i>- Didn't you leave together?</i>

22
00:00:54,304 --> 00:00:55,513
<i>They haven't come back yet.</i>

23
00:00:56,222 --> 00:00:59,517
<i>- I hope nothing bad happened to them.</i>
<i>- Like what happened to my mom, huh?</i>

24
00:00:59,601 --> 00:01:01,061
<i>Is it true?</i>

25
00:01:01,144 --> 00:01:03,605
<i>Did Auntie Wendy really go to jail</i>
<i>because of you?</i>

26
00:01:03,688 --> 00:01:05,148
<i>What case?</i>

27
00:01:05,231 --> 00:01:06,900
[OLSEN] <i>The estafa case, sir.</i>

28
00:01:06,983 --> 00:01:08,109
Right, Ma'am Greta?

29
00:01:10,487 --> 00:01:13,698
The estafa case
my mother got caught up in…

30
00:01:15,075 --> 00:01:17,577
It turns out Ma'am Greta
was the real culprit.

31
00:01:17,660 --> 00:01:18,995
Stop it.

32
00:01:19,079 --> 00:01:21,289
To avoid getting in trouble,

33
00:01:22,123 --> 00:01:24,709
you paid Aunt Wendy one million

34
00:01:25,418 --> 00:01:26,920
so she could take the blame.

35
00:01:28,004 --> 00:01:29,923
That's why she went to jail
instead of you.

36
00:01:30,006 --> 00:01:31,216
Ma.

37
00:01:31,299 --> 00:01:34,302
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

38
00:01:34,385 --> 00:01:35,595
- Tell me that's not--
- Liam.

39
00:01:37,597 --> 00:01:39,599
I'm the one who asked your mom for help.

40
00:01:41,518 --> 00:01:43,561
I needed money…

41
00:01:45,605 --> 00:01:47,690
because Olsen's life was in danger.

42
00:01:49,192 --> 00:01:52,987
No one forced me. I did it willingly.

43
00:01:53,988 --> 00:01:57,534
So don't be mad at your mom.
It's not her fault.

44
00:01:57,617 --> 00:02:01,412
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

45
00:02:01,496 --> 00:02:03,998
What's this now, Greta?

46
00:02:05,875 --> 00:02:07,710
This is what I've been trying to tell you.

47
00:02:09,295 --> 00:02:11,631
I'm sorry I lied.

48
00:02:12,882 --> 00:02:15,844
I told you I'd paid the investors.

49
00:02:15,927 --> 00:02:17,262
But it's not true.

50
00:02:18,054 --> 00:02:21,808
I wasn't able to pay them.
How could I pay them?

51
00:02:21,891 --> 00:02:24,811
All our money is gone because of bad luck

52
00:02:24,894 --> 00:02:27,063
and my string of bad investments.

53
00:02:27,147 --> 00:02:28,273
That's why…

54
00:02:29,232 --> 00:02:32,694
when they filed an estafa case against me…

55
00:02:32,777 --> 00:02:36,781
When Mama needed your help
because I got sick,

56
00:02:37,490 --> 00:02:41,202
you knew she'd do anything
for me as my mother.

57
00:02:42,704 --> 00:02:44,539
You took advantage of her.

58
00:02:45,665 --> 00:02:48,293
- Is that it?
- That's enough. Enough.

59
00:02:48,835 --> 00:02:51,296
So it's true?

60
00:02:52,755 --> 00:02:56,050
I didn't want to go to jail, Liam.

61
00:02:56,134 --> 00:02:58,887
I didn't want to be separated
from you and your dad.

62
00:02:59,637 --> 00:03:02,181
I got scared. I didn't know what to do.

63
00:03:02,265 --> 00:03:05,310
That's why I talked to Wendy.

64
00:03:05,393 --> 00:03:07,729
I told her I'd make it up to her.

65
00:03:09,439 --> 00:03:11,774
I kept my promise to her.

66
00:03:11,858 --> 00:03:14,110
I paid her another one million.

67
00:03:14,193 --> 00:03:15,612
I kept my promise!

68
00:03:15,695 --> 00:03:18,948
I kept my end of the deal! Why are you
throwing me under the bus, Wendy?!

69
00:03:19,032 --> 00:03:21,910
Is that how you really think of
my mother, Ma'am Greta?

70
00:03:23,328 --> 00:03:25,038
I thought you were friends?

71
00:03:26,706 --> 00:03:28,958
You think you can just buy us with money?

72
00:03:29,042 --> 00:03:31,044
If I hadn't helped you,

73
00:03:31,127 --> 00:03:32,837
you wouldn't be together now.

74
00:03:32,921 --> 00:03:34,589
If it weren't for me,

75
00:03:34,672 --> 00:03:37,091
you'd have been dead
a long time ago, Olsen!

76
00:03:37,175 --> 00:03:39,219
- [OLSEN] Ma.
- Greta.

77
00:03:41,346 --> 00:03:45,975
Why don't you just apologize
to Olsen and Wendy?

78
00:03:46,059 --> 00:03:49,103
Huh? Why would I apologize?

79
00:03:49,187 --> 00:03:52,148
Shouldn't they be thanking me instead?

80
00:03:53,733 --> 00:03:54,984
And you!

81
00:03:55,610 --> 00:03:58,947
You're taking their side
like they're your family!

82
00:03:59,030 --> 00:04:01,616
We're your family! Me and Liam!

83
00:04:01,699 --> 00:04:04,035
I'm your wife, Magnus!

84
00:04:04,118 --> 00:04:09,415
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

85
00:04:19,717 --> 00:04:21,052
Well, Liam?

86
00:04:21,135 --> 00:04:22,220
Stop it.

87
00:04:22,303 --> 00:04:26,391
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

88
00:04:34,774 --> 00:04:41,281
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

89
00:05:11,144 --> 00:05:18,109
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

90
00:05:33,833 --> 00:05:40,590
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

91
00:05:40,673 --> 00:05:41,841
Command, be advised.

92
00:05:41,924 --> 00:05:44,969
<i>The activity area and shoreline</i>
<i>are heavily guarded.</i>

93
00:05:45,053 --> 00:05:46,721
<i>They're armed with rifles.</i>

94
00:05:46,804 --> 00:05:49,015
<i>Three people are patrolling</i>
<i>the north perimeter</i>

95
00:05:49,098 --> 00:05:50,808
in the villa areas. Over.

96
00:05:51,559 --> 00:05:54,437
Copy. Do you have visual on the hostages?

97
00:05:55,021 --> 00:05:58,483
Command, negative.
No visual on the hostages. Over.

98
00:05:58,566 --> 00:05:59,484
Copy.

99
00:05:59,567 --> 00:06:01,277
Maintain observation of the area.

100
00:06:01,360 --> 00:06:03,571
Report any movements right away. Over.

101
00:06:03,654 --> 00:06:04,822
Yes, sir.

102
00:06:04,906 --> 00:06:08,868
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

103
00:06:08,951 --> 00:06:10,495
[MUSIC FADES]

104
00:06:16,751 --> 00:06:21,881
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

105
00:06:40,149 --> 00:06:41,317
Dude.

106
00:06:43,236 --> 00:06:45,071
You should get some rest.

107
00:06:45,154 --> 00:06:46,656
I'll keep a lookout.

108
00:06:49,117 --> 00:06:51,577
We need to find a chance

109
00:06:52,870 --> 00:06:54,831
to escape this island.

110
00:06:54,914 --> 00:07:01,170
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

111
00:07:08,386 --> 00:07:09,387
Son,

112
00:07:10,930 --> 00:07:12,723
try to understand me.

113
00:07:15,309 --> 00:07:16,352
Liam.

114
00:07:17,019 --> 00:07:18,855
Your mom is talking to you.

115
00:07:29,198 --> 00:07:31,117
How could you do that, Ma?

116
00:07:34,745 --> 00:07:37,748
You should've taken responsibility
for your actions.

117
00:07:42,462 --> 00:07:44,422
Would you rather

118
00:07:44,505 --> 00:07:46,424
I'd gone to jail

119
00:07:47,049 --> 00:07:49,719
instead of Olsen's mother?

120
00:07:51,554 --> 00:07:53,764
I had no choice, Liam.

121
00:07:54,765 --> 00:08:01,772
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

122
00:08:06,068 --> 00:08:07,737
[SNIFFLES, SOBS SOFTLY]

123
00:08:10,072 --> 00:08:11,866
[GRETA SNIFFLES]

124
00:08:13,409 --> 00:08:14,869
You had no choice?

125
00:08:15,661 --> 00:08:18,789
What else aren't you telling me?

126
00:08:21,834 --> 00:08:24,295
You said our money was stolen.

127
00:08:28,299 --> 00:08:30,092
How would that happen?

128
00:08:31,219 --> 00:08:32,762
What's done is done.

129
00:08:33,346 --> 00:08:35,431
There's nothing we can do anymore.

130
00:08:35,515 --> 00:08:37,767
What kind of answer is that?

131
00:08:40,853 --> 00:08:43,397
If those investments were legitimate,

132
00:08:43,481 --> 00:08:44,732
you should've told me.

133
00:08:44,815 --> 00:08:46,526
Why didn't you tell me?

134
00:08:49,320 --> 00:08:52,073
I trusted you with our finances.

135
00:08:52,156 --> 00:08:54,867
You and I were supposed to be
partners in the company.

136
00:08:56,369 --> 00:08:58,579
I'm in charge of managing the operations,

137
00:08:59,455 --> 00:09:00,831
and you…

138
00:09:02,416 --> 00:09:05,294
you just threw all our money away.

139
00:09:05,920 --> 00:09:09,757
We have so many bank accounts.
What happened to all of them?

140
00:09:10,508 --> 00:09:11,842
Magnus…

141
00:09:13,302 --> 00:09:14,762
I got addicted.

142
00:09:14,845 --> 00:09:16,514
What do you mean, Greta?

143
00:09:16,597 --> 00:09:18,224
Addicted to what?

144
00:09:18,307 --> 00:09:20,351
Gambling.

145
00:09:20,434 --> 00:09:24,272
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

146
00:09:24,355 --> 00:09:28,859
So aside from bad investments,
you gambled our money away.

147
00:09:30,152 --> 00:09:33,864
Because I wanted to earn back
the money we lost.

148
00:09:35,616 --> 00:09:37,451
At first, I was winning,

149
00:09:37,535 --> 00:09:40,246
and then I kept losing.

150
00:09:40,329 --> 00:09:42,748
I kept going until…

151
00:09:44,250 --> 00:09:47,003
I really wanted to get our money back.

152
00:09:48,754 --> 00:09:50,881
[SOBS] Sometimes,

153
00:09:51,591 --> 00:09:54,969
I'll stay at the hotel
for two to three days

154
00:09:55,052 --> 00:09:56,387
just to play in the casino.

155
00:09:56,470 --> 00:09:58,014
Why didn't I know?

156
00:09:58,097 --> 00:09:59,473
[GRETA BREATHING HEAVILY]

157
00:09:59,557 --> 00:10:03,144
Where was I when all these things
were happening to you?

158
00:10:03,227 --> 00:10:05,813
You were busy having an affair!

159
00:10:05,896 --> 00:10:09,358
[SOFT TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

160
00:10:09,942 --> 00:10:11,819
Aside from the hope

161
00:10:11,902 --> 00:10:14,614
of getting back the money we lost,

162
00:10:16,907 --> 00:10:19,076
it also made me forget

163
00:10:19,952 --> 00:10:22,997
that you were fooling around.

164
00:10:25,458 --> 00:10:26,584
Wow.

165
00:10:27,501 --> 00:10:29,337
Now you're using me as an excuse.

166
00:10:30,630 --> 00:10:32,757
You got me into this trouble.

167
00:10:32,840 --> 00:10:34,634
What do you mean, Magnus?

168
00:10:34,717 --> 00:10:37,386
We're involved in this mess together.

169
00:10:41,390 --> 00:10:42,683
[BREATH QUIVERING]

170
00:10:42,767 --> 00:10:44,435
Magnus, come back here!

171
00:10:44,518 --> 00:10:46,979
You wanted to talk about this, right?

172
00:10:47,063 --> 00:10:50,399
[BREATH QUIVERS, SOBS]

173
00:10:50,483 --> 00:10:56,614
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

174
00:10:56,697 --> 00:10:57,782
[CRIES]

175
00:10:58,991 --> 00:11:03,704
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

176
00:11:06,040 --> 00:11:09,877
Son, do you think your grandpa
will be able to find this place?

177
00:11:09,960 --> 00:11:12,254
Do you think he'll be able
to come back here?

178
00:11:16,550 --> 00:11:18,135
Sorry, Ma, but…

179
00:11:19,845 --> 00:11:22,431
honestly, I don't have an answer to that.

180
00:11:24,642 --> 00:11:25,976
[INHALES DEEPLY]

181
00:11:26,060 --> 00:11:28,896
I hope he remains safe.

182
00:11:28,979 --> 00:11:30,064
I hope so too.

183
00:11:30,981 --> 00:11:32,400
H-Hopefully.

184
00:11:32,483 --> 00:11:33,359
I really hope so.

185
00:11:34,193 --> 00:11:35,945
Don't worry, it's Grandpa Ben.

186
00:11:36,028 --> 00:11:37,405
[SNIFFS]

187
00:11:37,488 --> 00:11:38,656
He can do it.

188
00:11:43,285 --> 00:11:44,787
Ms. Wendy.

189
00:11:45,746 --> 00:11:48,040
We need to clean your wound.

190
00:11:49,500 --> 00:11:50,793
Thanks, Ice.

191
00:11:51,877 --> 00:11:53,254
[WENDY] Ice.

192
00:11:54,004 --> 00:11:57,800
Can you tell Greta and Magnus
that I want to talk to them?

193
00:11:58,717 --> 00:12:00,344
Okay.

194
00:12:00,428 --> 00:12:01,679
I'll tell them.

195
00:12:06,058 --> 00:12:08,352
Ma, you don't have to feel guilty.

196
00:12:09,311 --> 00:12:10,271
I know you.

197
00:12:10,354 --> 00:12:12,690
Ma, if someone has to feel guilty,

198
00:12:13,524 --> 00:12:15,860
it should be Ma'am Greta, not you.

199
00:12:15,943 --> 00:12:17,445
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

200
00:12:17,528 --> 00:12:21,907
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

201
00:12:21,991 --> 00:12:23,242
Auntie Wendy.

202
00:12:24,243 --> 00:12:25,536
Olsen.

203
00:12:26,328 --> 00:12:27,413
I'm sorry.

204
00:12:30,666 --> 00:12:32,293
Olsen.

205
00:12:33,919 --> 00:12:36,130
It's not Liam's fault.

206
00:12:37,381 --> 00:12:39,633
No one is at fault here.

207
00:12:39,717 --> 00:12:44,555
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

208
00:12:44,638 --> 00:12:45,723
Olsen.

209
00:12:46,640 --> 00:12:48,017
I'll admit it.

210
00:12:52,771 --> 00:12:54,690
Mama was wrong.

211
00:12:54,773 --> 00:12:58,402
[SOFT TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

212
00:12:58,486 --> 00:12:59,778
[SCOFFS]

213
00:12:59,862 --> 00:13:00,696
Okay.

214
00:13:02,448 --> 00:13:05,034
Okay, you admitted it.

215
00:13:05,117 --> 00:13:06,202
Now what?

216
00:13:07,369 --> 00:13:09,121
What do you want me to say? "Thank you"?

217
00:13:11,582 --> 00:13:12,791
You admit it, huh?

218
00:13:14,376 --> 00:13:17,004
Liam, in case you forgot,
you still owe us for another thing.

219
00:13:17,087 --> 00:13:18,547
What do you want me to do?

220
00:13:19,924 --> 00:13:22,343
- Kneel in front of you?
- Wow.

221
00:13:22,426 --> 00:13:25,054
Are you for real?
You're really asking me that?

222
00:13:25,137 --> 00:13:28,474
If you kneel, will my mom's
gunshot wound disappear?

223
00:13:28,557 --> 00:13:30,768
What? Answer me.

224
00:13:30,851 --> 00:13:33,020
Olsen, Liam, stop it.

225
00:13:33,854 --> 00:13:35,356
Your mom is right there.

226
00:13:36,190 --> 00:13:38,150
[LUNA] Have some respect for Ms. Wendy.

227
00:13:40,319 --> 00:13:42,988
We shouldn't be fighting.

228
00:13:43,614 --> 00:13:45,241
Yes, we're safe right now.

229
00:13:46,617 --> 00:13:47,618
But until when?

230
00:13:49,662 --> 00:13:53,582
Can we first think of a way
to escape this island?

231
00:13:53,666 --> 00:14:00,506
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

232
00:14:03,759 --> 00:14:06,178
What about the other hostages?

233
00:14:07,096 --> 00:14:10,766
We know that even if they pay the ransom,

234
00:14:10,849 --> 00:14:12,560
they'll still be killed.

235
00:14:20,109 --> 00:14:21,861
[OLSEN EXHALES DEEPLY]

236
00:14:36,584 --> 00:14:37,418
[FIN] Wait.

237
00:14:37,501 --> 00:14:39,628
Where did those come from?

238
00:14:39,712 --> 00:14:40,629
Chief!

239
00:14:41,171 --> 00:14:42,923
- Chief! Chief!
- [BEN] They're here.

240
00:14:43,007 --> 00:14:45,551
Chief, let's go! Let's leave this island!

241
00:14:45,634 --> 00:14:46,844
Chief!

242
00:14:49,096 --> 00:14:52,600
You know that I can't leave
my family behind.

243
00:14:53,183 --> 00:14:54,226
You should go.

244
00:14:55,227 --> 00:14:57,771
Go and save yourself.

245
00:14:57,855 --> 00:14:59,815
You have parents
who are worrying about you.

246
00:15:01,025 --> 00:15:01,942
Chief.

247
00:15:04,194 --> 00:15:06,447
You know that I'm adopted, right?

248
00:15:07,865 --> 00:15:09,825
Are you saying

249
00:15:11,160 --> 00:15:13,329
they never treated you like their own son?

250
00:15:13,412 --> 00:15:15,623
At first, they did.

251
00:15:15,706 --> 00:15:19,126
But when they had their own child,

252
00:15:20,044 --> 00:15:21,629
everything changed.

253
00:15:21,712 --> 00:15:26,175
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

254
00:15:26,258 --> 00:15:27,384
Chief.

255
00:15:28,177 --> 00:15:29,762
You and Olsen,

256
00:15:29,845 --> 00:15:31,430
you're my family.

257
00:15:38,979 --> 00:15:40,147
All right.

258
00:15:40,230 --> 00:15:41,649
- Chief.
- [BEN] Okay.

259
00:15:41,732 --> 00:15:44,193
Let's go and find them.

260
00:15:46,862 --> 00:15:48,614
Ice, are you sure you want to come?

261
00:15:49,239 --> 00:15:51,325
I want to know if Bogs is safe.

262
00:15:51,408 --> 00:15:52,576
Also,

263
00:15:52,660 --> 00:15:55,287
if one of you gets injured, I can help.

264
00:15:55,371 --> 00:15:57,039
I hope that doesn't happen.

265
00:15:57,122 --> 00:15:58,958
Luna knows where the staff are.

266
00:15:59,041 --> 00:16:01,418
We'll take as many as we can.

267
00:16:02,252 --> 00:16:05,047
Okay, we'll take the hostages
in the banquet hall.

268
00:16:05,130 --> 00:16:08,509
- Just remember, we'll meet here after.
- [OLSEN] Yes.

269
00:16:08,592 --> 00:16:10,094
Bring everyone you can save.

270
00:16:10,177 --> 00:16:11,345
Okay.

271
00:16:11,929 --> 00:16:14,431
We'll try to look for Fin and Grandpa too.

272
00:16:14,515 --> 00:16:15,933
- Okay.
- Okay.

273
00:16:16,016 --> 00:16:17,434
- [LIAM] Let's go.
- [OLSEN] Come on.

274
00:16:17,977 --> 00:16:19,186
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

275
00:16:19,269 --> 00:16:20,437
[LUNA CHUCKLES]

276
00:16:21,105 --> 00:16:22,064
- [LIAM] What?
- What?

277
00:16:22,147 --> 00:16:23,941
[CLAPS] Keep doing that.

278
00:16:24,024 --> 00:16:26,110
Try to be civil, bro.

279
00:16:26,652 --> 00:16:27,945
So…

280
00:16:28,529 --> 00:16:30,364
- One, two--
- We're just wasting time.

281
00:16:30,447 --> 00:16:31,573
Let's go.

282
00:16:35,828 --> 00:16:36,954
Sorry, bro.

283
00:16:45,129 --> 00:16:46,213
[GRUNTS]

284
00:16:48,507 --> 00:16:50,009
[GRUNTS]

285
00:16:50,718 --> 00:16:51,969
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

286
00:16:52,052 --> 00:16:53,429
[HAPPY EXHALES DEEPLY]

287
00:16:55,764 --> 00:16:56,807
[JOY SIGHS]

288
00:16:57,683 --> 00:16:59,810
It's the end.

289
00:16:59,893 --> 00:17:00,853
[SNIFFLES]

290
00:17:00,936 --> 00:17:02,104
What?

291
00:17:02,187 --> 00:17:03,731
It's the end for us?

292
00:17:06,817 --> 00:17:08,485
It's the end of the month.

293
00:17:08,569 --> 00:17:10,738
Time to receive our salary, Manager Happy.

294
00:17:12,698 --> 00:17:14,033
My goodness, Joy.

295
00:17:14,992 --> 00:17:17,411
If we weren't hostages right now,
I would've murdered you.

296
00:17:17,494 --> 00:17:19,788
[HAPPY] You're really
thinking about that right now?

297
00:17:24,293 --> 00:17:25,252
[JOY SOBS]

298
00:17:25,335 --> 00:17:27,963
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

299
00:17:28,047 --> 00:17:30,466
I'm just worried about my father.

300
00:17:31,133 --> 00:17:34,428
[SNIFFLES] He only has me to depend on.

301
00:17:34,511 --> 00:17:36,263
He's disabled now.

302
00:17:39,725 --> 00:17:40,726
Me too.

303
00:17:41,351 --> 00:17:43,395
My father relies on me now.

304
00:17:45,856 --> 00:17:47,024
[LOVE] For me…

305
00:17:49,526 --> 00:17:52,237
I'm paying for two
of my nephews' schooling.

306
00:17:53,030 --> 00:17:56,742
My husband left me a long time ago.

307
00:17:58,702 --> 00:18:02,623
My child only has me as a parent.

308
00:18:03,832 --> 00:18:05,334
[SNIFFLES, SOBS]

309
00:18:06,210 --> 00:18:11,799
MJ won't have any parents left if I die.

310
00:18:12,841 --> 00:18:15,803
My poor kid.

311
00:18:17,429 --> 00:18:21,016
My baby will be alone.

312
00:18:23,227 --> 00:18:26,188
[HAPPY SOBBING]

313
00:18:31,276 --> 00:18:34,613
[ALL CRYING]

314
00:18:37,908 --> 00:18:39,076
Maddie…

315
00:18:41,078 --> 00:18:45,124
always remember what Mommy tells you.

316
00:18:46,667 --> 00:18:49,878
You can do anything you want…?

317
00:18:49,962 --> 00:18:53,465
If I believe in myself and…

318
00:18:54,550 --> 00:18:57,302
- Never…
- And never give up.

319
00:18:57,386 --> 00:18:59,346
- Yes.
- [MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

320
00:18:59,429 --> 00:19:00,597
Never give up.

321
00:19:00,681 --> 00:19:02,266
The three of us

322
00:19:03,934 --> 00:19:05,769
will never give up.

323
00:19:08,272 --> 00:19:09,314
Never.

324
00:19:13,110 --> 00:19:17,739
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

325
00:19:18,448 --> 00:19:19,575
Chief.

326
00:19:20,367 --> 00:19:21,827
- Chief.
- Oh?

327
00:19:21,910 --> 00:19:23,287
Where could the cops be?

328
00:19:23,370 --> 00:19:24,413
I don't know.

329
00:19:25,038 --> 00:19:29,293
What if the hostage takers
have already killed them?

330
00:19:29,376 --> 00:19:30,919
I hope they haven't.

331
00:19:34,089 --> 00:19:35,257
I hope not too.

332
00:19:35,340 --> 00:19:36,466
Of course.

333
00:19:36,550 --> 00:19:38,177
They could be around.

334
00:19:38,260 --> 00:19:39,344
Yeah.

335
00:19:41,305 --> 00:19:42,973
- Put your guns down!
- Hands in the air!

336
00:19:43,056 --> 00:19:49,021
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

337
00:19:49,104 --> 00:19:50,397
- Chief, chief…
- Fin…

338
00:19:51,315 --> 00:19:53,233
Put your gun down. Down.

339
00:19:54,067 --> 00:19:55,360
Down.

340
00:20:04,578 --> 00:20:06,455
Sir, believe me!

341
00:20:06,538 --> 00:20:07,956
We're not the hostage takers!

342
00:20:08,040 --> 00:20:09,082
Shut your mouth!

343
00:20:10,292 --> 00:20:12,336
[MAN ON RADIO] <i>Are those</i>
<i>the ones you caught, sir?</i>

344
00:20:14,963 --> 00:20:16,173
Yes.

345
00:20:28,101 --> 00:20:29,436
<i>Confirmed, sir.</i>

346
00:20:29,519 --> 00:20:32,773
<i>That's Ben Bonifacio,</i>
<i>Head of Security at La Playa Roja.</i>

347
00:20:32,856 --> 00:20:34,942
<i>And that's Fin Muñoz.</i>
<i>He's a security officer.</i>

348
00:20:42,074 --> 00:20:43,575
Let them go.

349
00:20:46,203 --> 00:20:47,454
[FIN GRUNTS]

350
00:20:49,039 --> 00:20:51,750
I told you, right?
But you wouldn't listen.

351
00:20:51,833 --> 00:20:54,711
You're the one who doesn't listen!
I said shut your mouth!

352
00:20:59,049 --> 00:21:00,467
Ben Bonifacio.

353
00:21:00,550 --> 00:21:01,718
Yes, sir.

354
00:21:02,678 --> 00:21:04,972
- Fin Muñoz.
- Sir.

355
00:21:06,390 --> 00:21:07,557
We're here to save you.

356
00:21:07,641 --> 00:21:08,850
[TRIUMPHANT MUSIC PLAYING]

357
00:21:08,934 --> 00:21:10,352
Sir, thanks. Thank you, sir.

358
00:21:11,186 --> 00:21:13,939
- Thank you.
- Sir, thank you.

359
00:21:14,022 --> 00:21:15,816
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

360
00:21:15,899 --> 00:21:16,733
Thank you.

361
00:21:16,817 --> 00:21:18,986
- Sir, thank you.
- Thank you.

362
00:21:19,945 --> 00:21:21,571
Thank you.

363
00:21:21,655 --> 00:21:22,781
Chief.

364
00:21:22,864 --> 00:21:25,826
[TRIUMPHANT MUSIC CONTINUES]

365
00:21:29,329 --> 00:21:35,127
[HEAVY FOOTSTEPS]

366
00:21:42,259 --> 00:21:49,266
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

367
00:21:56,940 --> 00:21:58,066
Hurry up over there!

368
00:22:00,694 --> 00:22:02,154
Bring that upstairs, okay?

369
00:22:05,991 --> 00:22:07,826
[REPORTER] Sir, can we get an interview?

370
00:22:07,909 --> 00:22:13,081
- [POLICE] Just ask your questions later!
- [REPORTERS] Sir! What happened to them?

371
00:22:13,165 --> 00:22:16,626
- [POLICE 1] Stay back, please!
- [REPORTER] Are they the only survivors?

372
00:22:16,710 --> 00:22:18,462
[REPORTER] Sir, please!

373
00:22:18,545 --> 00:22:21,590
- [REPORTER] Don't push us!
- [POLICE 2] It's off limits! Stay back!

374
00:22:21,673 --> 00:22:23,675
[REPORTER] Sir, are there other survivors?

375
00:22:23,759 --> 00:22:25,844
- [POLICE 1] Stay over there!
- [REPORTER] Don't push us!

376
00:22:25,927 --> 00:22:29,639
- [REPORTER] Just a few questions, sir!
- [POLICE 1] Interviews aren't allowed.

377
00:22:29,723 --> 00:22:30,891
Stay back, please!

378
00:22:30,974 --> 00:22:32,184
- [LINE RINGING]
- [BEEPS]

379
00:22:35,020 --> 00:22:36,021
Lucas.

380
00:22:36,104 --> 00:22:37,147
Boss Emil.

381
00:22:37,230 --> 00:22:38,565
<i>What happened to you?</i>

382
00:22:38,648 --> 00:22:40,192
I've been calling you.

383
00:22:40,859 --> 00:22:43,862
<i>Did you get the diamonds from Ona Chan?</i>

384
00:22:43,945 --> 00:22:44,946
I have them.

385
00:22:45,030 --> 00:22:46,823
Then come back here.

386
00:22:46,907 --> 00:22:48,700
It might not be possible yet, sir.

387
00:22:48,784 --> 00:22:49,951
Something happened.

388
00:22:50,827 --> 00:22:51,745
What?

389
00:22:51,828 --> 00:22:53,955
<i>How did Dr. Morillo,</i>

390
00:22:54,039 --> 00:22:57,209
his wife, and Jules Santos escape?

391
00:22:57,292 --> 00:23:00,462
They were brought to a hospital
here in Alicante.

392
00:23:00,545 --> 00:23:01,922
<i>They're guarded by the police,</i>

393
00:23:02,005 --> 00:23:05,592
and I'm sure there are
police officers over there too.

394
00:23:05,675 --> 00:23:12,265
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

395
00:23:18,021 --> 00:23:20,941
[BEN] <i>Every area</i>
<i>we'll pass through has guards.</i>

396
00:23:21,024 --> 00:23:24,653
<i>It's safer if we go through the side.</i>

397
00:23:24,736 --> 00:23:27,030
[LIAM] <i>With everything I found out</i>
<i>about my mother,</i>

398
00:23:27,114 --> 00:23:30,117
<i>I'm so confused about what to believe.</i>

399
00:23:30,200 --> 00:23:32,786
<i>When I come back,</i>
<i>I'll bring our staff with me.</i>

400
00:23:32,869 --> 00:23:35,372
[OLSEN] <i>We can't just wait</i>
<i>for their next move.</i>

401
00:23:35,455 --> 00:23:36,665
<i>- Olsen!</i>
- [GOON SHOUTS]

402
00:23:36,748 --> 00:23:38,041
<i>- Olsen!</i>
- [GUNSHOT]

403
00:23:38,125 --> 00:23:41,586
[EMIL] <i>Your lives will be</i>
<i>the price for interfering!</i>

404
00:23:41,670 --> 00:23:43,713
<i>We're all going to die here.</i>

405
00:23:44,214 --> 00:23:45,841
[LUNA] <i>What do we do, man?</i>

406
00:23:45,924 --> 00:23:47,551
<i>Looks like the guards aren't leaving.</i>

407
00:23:48,218 --> 00:23:50,387
<i>You need to make sure they stay there.</i>

408
00:23:50,470 --> 00:23:53,682
- <i>Please have mercy on us, sir!</i>
- [STAFF SOBBING]

409
00:23:54,724 --> 00:23:59,813
[RAPID GUNFIRE]
